    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-08-31T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-08-31T14:00:00-05:00" n="649"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d649">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">812.6363/6095: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Daniels</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-08-31T13:00:00-06:00"
                            >August 31, 1939—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 5:12 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>235. Upon arrival by air here yesterday Castillo Nájera said, in summary, that
                    the companies had taken no steps to renew the suspended oil conversations. He
                    added that he believed the decision as to war or peace in Europe would be taken
                    by Saturday. He further said that the Mexican political situation was not of
                    interest to the United States as far as he could see from public opinion
                    there.</p>
                <p>Newspaper reports forwarded by this morning’s air mail.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Daniels</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
